  "details": "MailEnable versions prior to 10.55 contain a reflected cross-site scripting vulnerability in the webmail interface that allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary JavaScript in a victim's browser by crafting a malicious URL. Attackers can inject malicious code through the StartDate parameter in the FreeBusy.aspx form, which is not properly sanitized before being embedded into dynamically generated JavaScript.",
